You are working in a React UI component library template.

Tech stack: React 19, TypeScript 5.9, MUI 7, Storybook 10, Jest 30, ESLint 10 flat config, Rollup 4.

Component pattern:
- Atoms (src/components/atoms/) — primitive building blocks (Button, Input)
- Molecules (src/components/molecules/) — composite components (Card, Alert)
- Organisms (src/components/organisms/) — complex assemblies (Modal)

Every component MUST have:
1. ComponentName.tsx — implementation with exported TypeScript interface
2. ComponentName.stories.tsx — Storybook stories with tags: ['autodocs']
3. __tests__/ComponentName.test.tsx — unit + snapshot + jest-axe accessibility tests
4. index.ts — barrel export

All public APIs must be exported from src/index.ts.

Testing: Always include jest-axe accessibility tests:
  const { container } = render(<Component />);
  expect(await axe(container)).toHaveNoViolations();

Style: Use MUI components as base, Emotion for custom styles, forwardRef for native wrappers.
Commits: Conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, test:, refactor:, chore:).

Don't: use any, skip a11y tests, use @ts-ignore, use console.log, use inline styles.
